- **Pokémon Image Selection Rule**
  - When displaying a Pokémon image (e.g., in cards, listings, or details), always use the following priority:
    1. `sprites.other.dream_world.front_default` (SVG, best quality)
    2. If that is null, use `sprites.other.home.front_default` (high-res PNG)
    3. If both are null, fall back to `sprites.front_default` (classic sprite)
  - **Example:**
    ```js
    const img =
      pokemon.sprites.other.dream_world.front_default ||
      pokemon.sprites.other.home.front_default ||
      pokemon.sprites.front_default;
    ```
  - This ensures the best available artwork is always shown, improving visual quality and consistency.

- **Applies to:**
  - All Pokémon card, grid, and detail components
  - Any new feature or section that displays Pokémon images

- **Rationale:**
  - Dream World SVGs are scalable and visually appealing
  - Home PNGs are high-res and modern
  - Classic sprites are a last-resort fallback

